                  <persName id="t18251208-99-person560">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BALL
               <interp inst="t18251208-99-person560" type="surname" value="BALL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-99-person560" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-99-person560" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Bow-street patrol. I apprehended the prisoner in Broad-street, St. Giles', on the 16th of November, about half-past five o'clock in the evening, he appeared very bulky - I found two pint pots round his body, and two in his bat - a quart pot dropped from him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18251208-99-person561">
                  DANIEL 
                  REARDON
               <interp inst="t18251208-99-person561" type="surname" value="REARDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-99-person561" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18251208-99-person561" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. I was in company with Ball, and saw the prisoner drop a quart, and a pint pot - two others were found in his bat, and another round his body.</p>
               <p>EDWARD SMITH. I am a <rs id="t18251208-99-viclabel497" type="occupation">victualler</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18251208-99-victim559 t18251208-99-viclabel497"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18251208-99-crimeloc498">Compton-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18251208-99-crimeloc498" type="placeName" value="Compton-street"></interp>
